// zellij-login layout — minimal "shell with persistence" UX.
//
// One plain pane for your shell, one line at the bottom showing mode +
// session name (the zellij:compact-bar built-in). No tab bar, no extra
// status rows, no nagging — so zellij feels like your terminal with
// session persistence, not a multiplexer.
//
// Mouse works out of the box (configured via `mouse_mode true` in
// config.kdl, not here). Session-manager, plugin-manager, and everything
// else remain reachable via Ctrl+o.
//
// Why this file and not a config flag? zellij has no "hide_tab_bar"
// switch — this is the supported way to hide it (see zellij-org/zellij
// issues #694, #2172, #4504). The layout is the contract.
//
// Installed by https://github.com/yigitkonur/zellij-login
layout {
    pane
    pane size=1 borderless=true {
        plugin location="zellij:compact-bar"
    }
}
